(Principle
    "Intent is the cornerstone of all agent activity. If any agent needs to know what to do, they fall back on intent. The intent protocol will soon become the almost exclusive form of psyche-agent interaction; the agent's only role is to clarify intent and capture intent. Action follows mechanically from intent that is clear enough to create signal."
    "the intent protocol will soon become the almost exclusive form of interaction between the psyche and agents. The agent's only role will be to clarify intent and capture intent. And everything else will happen mechanically from the intent. So even something like, do we intend this to become architecture? Is the agent asking for clarification on intent? Once the intent is stated, then the actions just happen. Because whatever intent is clear enough to create enough signal to warrant action becomes automatic action. So intent is like the cornerstone of all agent activity. If any agent needs to know what to do, then they fall back on intent."
    "The full framing of the intent-driven workspace: agents clarify and capture intent; everything else is mechanical execution of stated intent. This statement is the keystone for everything in ESSENCE and the intent layer."
    Maximum
