(Decision
    "The timestamp format on intent records is too long and noisy. The trailing :00Z (seconds + UTC marker) is redundant — every timestamp has it. The hyphens inside the date make the string longer than needed for an agent-readable field. The T date-time separator does not visually read as a delimiter (it looks like part of the number 17T13). A more compact format is wanted. Open: which format. Once decided, a script rewrites existing timestamps."
    "I don't really like the date formatting. Maybe you can use a script to, like, redo that. It seems a little bit excessive. … what's the last colon zero zero Z? Everything has that, the same suffix on every single timestamp. … And do we really need all these hyphens? … this T is actually… What is this format, anyway? … What really compact time format can we use? And this whole zero zero Z at the end is really just annoying. Like, what the fuck is that about?"
    "Format complaint with several specific issues: redundant :00Z suffix, hyphens make string longer, T doesn't read as a delimiter. Decision is to switch formats; choice is open until psyche picks from proposed options."
    Maximum
    2026-05-19T18:00:00Z)

(Decision
