(Decision
    "Vocabulary clarification — three terms, distinct surfaces. (1) 'Intent log' = the NOTA-format records in intent/<topic>.nota. Raw psyche statements, append-only, lock-free. (2) 'Intent file' = the per-repo INTENT.md at a repo root. Prose, mostly composed of summaries from the intent log, with verbatim psyche quotes interleaved. Like ARCHITECTURE.md but for intent. (3) 'Essence' = 'essential intent' — the highest, most universal psyche intent. Workspace ESSENCE.md is the workspace's essence; per-repo ESSENCE files (when they exist) are the project's essence. Same prose-of-summaries-plus-verbatim-quotes convention as intent files."
